==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Ensanguine
<hw>En*san"guine</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <def>To stain or
cover with blood; to make bloody, or of a blood-red color; <as>as, an
<ex>ensanguined</ex> hue</as>.</def> ⟦ldquo⟧The <xex>ensanguined</xex>
field.⟦rdquo⟧ <rj><au>Milton.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Ensate</ent>⟦br⟧
